From: Performance Patch Series
Subject: [PATCH 11/16] Cache gRPC read client at connection level

Bottleneck #11: ExecuteQueryInternalAsync creates a new
TokenProtectedReadClientManger (and thus a new BigQueryReadClient with
its own GrpcChannel) on every query execution. Each new channel pays
TCP + TLS + HTTP/2 establishment on its first RPC (~50-200ms), and the
previous channel is abandoned for GC finalization, leaking connections.

This is distinct from existing bottleneck #5 (credential-update
rebuild). Here the issue is that a brand-new client is constructed on
every single query, regardless of credential state.

The fix moves the TokenProtectedReadClientManger to the connection
level so it is created once and reused across all queries on that
connection. The UpdateToken delegate updates the shared instance's
credential when a token refresh occurs. The connection's Dispose()
method is updated to clean up the shared client.

---
 csharp/src/BigQueryConnection.cs | 35 +++---
 csharp/src/BigQueryStatement.cs  | 35 +++---

diff --git a/csharp/src/BigQueryConnection.cs b/csharp/src/BigQueryConnection.cs
index 68e05a3..d68717e 100644
--- a/csharp/src/BigQueryConnection.cs
+++ b/csharp/src/BigQueryConnection.cs
@@ -180,6 +180,8 @@ namespace AdbcDrivers.BigQuery
 
         internal GoogleCredential? Credential { get; private set; }
 
+        internal TokenProtectedReadClientManger? ReadClientManager { get; private set; }
+
         internal int MaxRetryAttempts { get; private set; } = 5;
 
         internal int RetryDelayMs { get; private set; } = 200;
@@ -407,6 +409,22 @@ namespace AdbcDrivers.BigQuery
                 }
 
                 Client = client;
+
+                // Create or update the shared gRPC read client
+                if (ReadClientManager == null)
+                {
+                    ReadClientManager = new TokenProtectedReadClientManger(Credential!);
+                    ReadClientManager.UpdateToken = () => Task.Run(() =>
+                    {
+                        SetCredential();
+                        ReadClientManager.UpdateCredential(Credential);
+                    });
+                }
+                else
+                {
+                    ReadClientManager.UpdateCredential(Credential!);
+                }
+
                 return client;
             }, ClassName + "." + nameof(Open));
         }
@@ -1709,6 +1727,11 @@ namespace AdbcDrivers.BigQuery
         {
             Client?.Dispose();
             Client = null;
+            // The ReadClientManager wraps a BigQueryReadClient (gRPC channel).
+            // We null the reference so it can be garbage-collected; the underlying
+            // gRPC channel will be cleaned up by the finalizer since
+            // BigQueryReadClient does not expose a public Dispose().
+            ReadClientManager = null;
             this.httpClient?.Dispose();
             this._fileActivityListener?.Dispose();
         }
